    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-26T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)/13937a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-26T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>524. For Eisenhardt from Metals Reserve. You are hereby authorized to act for
                    Metals Reserve Company in the purchase of <pb facs="0820" n="806"
                        xml:id="pg_806"/> Venezuelan industrial diamonds in the amount of $300,000
                    at prices set forth in detailed instructions being airmailed you today. These
                    prices will apply f.o.b. plane, Venezuelan airports and are the equivalent of
                    prices currently being paid in Brazil. A letter of credit is being opened with
                    Chase National Bank, providing for payment against Seller’s invoices,
                    certificates of weight and inspection signed by Eskenazi<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d677fn43">Leon Eskenazi, assigned to Venezuela by the Board of
                        Economic Warfare in connection with the diamond purchase program.</note> and
                    approved by you, and airline receipts. [Metals Reserve.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
